						<summary>

						<p><hi rend="italic">Capitals of the pillars in the temple of Siddhēśvara.</hi></p>						

						<p>These inscriptions state that the respective pillars on which they are engraved were caused to be made by <hi rend="bold">Gaḷatigeya Malliseṭṭi</hi> and his three sons <hi rend="bold">Karuva Siṁgiseṭṭi, Mūkiseṭṭi</hi> and <hi rend="bold">Mahadēvaseṭṭi.</hi> The characters belong to about the <hi rend="bold">13th century A.D.</hi></p>						

						<p>(B.K. No. 91 of 1932-33.)</p>						

						<p>North-West Pillar.</p>						

						</summary>
